Anytime little extra bits of time I’ve found lately has been spent on this painting ❤️ 
Anytime I do art my brain is always thinking about tattoos/drawings for other people and to be honest, it can make you feel really burnt out.. SO I decided it was time to work on something that was just for me. I haven’t painted since Covid shutdown so it’s been about 3 years.. I get so wrapped up in life and work and like a lot of anxiety (A LOT) it was super nice to just sit back, watch Unsolved Mysteries and just work on something that I really love just for myself.
And now that I’m done I’m literally going to go start drawing for tattoo appointments hahahaha (like literally right now) but truthfully I love tattooing and drawing and art in general, I just need to make some time for painting every once and a while because I forget how happy it makes me 😊 

Ps. This is a cat skull that I unfortunately found in my backyard last spring. I have a lot of feral cats that I feed and we try to provide shelter for. Sometimes, and I hate it, they die. But I found this skull and I keep it in my car so this little cat can go on adventures with me (mostly to work and Starbucks haha) but I hate that there are so many feral cats in this world who don’t have love so I just wanted to do this painting and let little feral kitty live forever. ❤️ 
.

Before and after! So happy to have met Christina, (she is so awesome!) though not under the best circumstances. She NEEDED a coverup and a single glance will tell you why! 
This is a perfect example on why you should look into your artist before getting tattooed. Always always always look at portfolios! Don’t believe that just because someone owns a shop they are capable of any style of tattoo. If you’re uncomfortable, leave. You don’t want to end up in this situation yourself. 
.

✨ 37 ✨ 
Getting older is weird cause I still feel like I’m 18, have no idea what I’m doing, what I should be doing, where life if going, what choices I should make etc.. but then I think shit, I’m creeping on 40 hahaha I’m an adult 🤯 
Sometimes I feel old but try to remember that in 20 years I’ll look back on this time and think of how young I was. Either way, I’m 37 and still working on all those things I was working on when I was 18, and that’s okay. Maybe we never get it all figured out but life keeps going and we have to be thankful we made it this far into the confusion ♥️
